msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 230
msgid "Have Jacques resist capture for as long as he can."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=lose
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 234
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 465
msgid "Getting taken before turn 15."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 247
msgid "He is being tossed about on the open seas in the middle of a storm."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 251
msgid "No, he's crawling away from a battlefield. Why is he even there?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 255
msgid "Ahh, the sacred treasure. Must... get... the... treasure."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 259
msgid ""
"Is that him? Where is he going? Why is it so desolate? Is no one else around?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 263
msgid "Who are they? No, WHAT are they??"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 267
msgid "Go away, you fiends! Go away!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 354
msgid "His home, all burnt down! And where is he? In the house? Noooo..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 357
msgid "... and then he'd wake up, drenched in sweat and excitement."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 361
msgid ""
"Such were the dreams that Jacques had, foretelling his fate or at least "
"betraying his desires for adventure at all costs. Big castles, powerful "
"kings, mighty mages and fair maidens occupied his mind. He would often even "
"talk aloud of his plans to make it big, someday."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 366
msgid ""
"His friends teased him about this, but not too much. After all, Jacques was "
"the son of Yves the Surly, a drunk but also the leader of a little band of "
"bandits that harassed the area around the village of Mosh. While this made "
"Jacques unpopular with the common folk, it also gave him a sheltered "
"existence."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 370
msgid ""
"Thus Jacques dreamt of the day that he could leave and move on to greater "
"things. And then, that day had arrived. Perhaps not quite as Jacques had "
"envisioned it, but one should not be too picky when it comes to fate."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 374
msgid ""
"A treasure ship was seen to have crashed onto a small island off the coast "
"not far from Mosh, or at least that was the rumor circulating around the "
"village pub. A treasure ship! Surely, that could be the ticket out of this "
"life of poverty!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 378
msgid ""
"Jacques called together his small band of ruffians and set off to the island "
"to investigate. And this is where our story begins..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 390
msgid ""
"Jacques finds himself on the small island, but with no promised riches in "
"sight."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 395
msgid ""
"Shielding his eyes from the evening sun to find the wrecked treasure ship, "
"he spots smaller boats coming ashore, and finally the facts click into "
"place. He has been tricked, and an unfortunate fate awaits him!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 400
msgid ""
"He sees not one or two, but three encampments around him. First, there are "
"the villagers who tricked him into coming to this island in the first place. "
"He also spots some farmers, who confirmed that they saw the shipwreck from "
"ashore and must be in on the scam. Finally, he sees what appears to be a "
"band of goblin traders. To top it all, a local infestation of mud slime also "
"seems to have developed on this island, but that is not necessarily bad "
"news. The other three groups are what he worries about: traders and traitors "
"- slime, the lot of them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 405
msgid ""
"Remember, there is a good price for each one taken! You may beat some sense "
"into them, but do not waste them. Most importantly, catch their snotty "
"little leader! He will fetch a handsome sum!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Greedy Villager
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 409
msgid "Money! Gimme money!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Greedy Farmer
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 413
msgid "Yes, money, and good riddance of that ruffian scum to boot!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Mud Slime
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 417
msgid "Gurgle! (Food!)"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Greedy Farmer
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 421
msgid ""
"Oh no! The island is infested with slime! How can this be? We have to get "
"rid of it, before it manages to find its way onto our shores!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 425
msgid ""
"Do not forget the grand prize, peasants! The little thieves is what we're "
"after, and surely we need not bother about some rubbish slime."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Mud Slime
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 430
msgid "Mrrrmm! (Hungry!)."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 434
msgid ""
"I am not the thief on this island! Unless you count our stealing your senses "
"with our clubs, you filthy goblins!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 443
msgid ""
"Jabb! Are you sure our rookie troops will be able to deal with these pesky "
"ruffians? We could also call for the more experienced mercenaries to wrap "
"this up quickly."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 447
msgid ""
"No need, boss! These punching bags will be easy to deal with. Frankly, I "
"wonder whether they're even worth the trouble of not squashing them like "
"bugs."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 451
msgid "I'm mightily tempted to squash you myself, goblin!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 455
msgid "Come and get me!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 461
msgid ""
"Have Jacques resist capture for as long as he can. (+ special bonus if "
"Jacques kills the Goblin Handler)"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 479
msgid "No slacking, boys, go get them!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 487
msgid ""
"Faster, men, faster! You're not going to let them escape you so easily, are "
"you?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Greedy Farmer
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 496
msgid "Ahh, shut up!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Greedy Farmer
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 502
msgid ""
"I have to say, that Goblin Handler might have been a good fighter, but at "
"least it's nice and quiet without him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 523
msgid ""
"Observing the enemy, Jacques notices that the goblin handler moves in a "
"carefully plotted pattern. He mostly tries to stay out of harm's way, the "
"coward, but every now and then he comes close to the fighting to yell out "
"commands to his troops."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 528
msgid ""
"Perhaps, if Jacques timed the attack correctly, he could confront the "
"handler without coming too close to the two Northern encampments."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 543
msgid ""
"You can run, twist and dodge all you want, but you will never escape us! The "
"villagers want you gone, and we want the gold!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 547
msgid "Like you said yourself a while ago: Come and get me!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 555
msgid ""
"Whatever happens, at least now I have proven my worth in cuts and bruises "
"and may hold my head high."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 566
msgid "Goblins! To me! Protect your leader!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 577
msgid ""
"You dare sneak around me? Men, come and help me get this one chained up!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 588
msgid "Did you see, men? That's how you tether a restless calf!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 605
msgid "Gotcha! Not so smug now, are you?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 610
msgid "Wha-? How did you manage to sneak up on me? That was..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 616
msgid "How could this happen to me? Gone forever..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 620
msgid "Well, he didn't die at my hand, but at least we got rid of him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [floating_text]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 652
msgid "<span color='green'>+1 melee attack</span>"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 656
msgid "Good riddance. Hey, I'm getting a hang of these weapon swings!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 680
msgid "Let me get rid of this slime for you amateurs! Shouldn't take long."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 712
msgid ""
"What does this gob of slime think it's doing? Wait, is it really attacking "
"me? Help, help!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 728
msgid "Hey! This thing can attack! Help, help!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 762
msgid "I cannot believe it! Killed by this stupid slime? Ahh, what shame..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 787
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 800
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 285
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 232
msgid "Aaaargh!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 791
msgid ""
"Ahh! Not as springy as I thought. No special sale for him then, just your "
"regular gallows..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 804
msgid ""
"Ahh, a feisty little character, indeed! That will do nicely for where I am "
"about to send him..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 835
msgid "Jabb! They will be easy pickings, you said."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 839
msgid ""
"Well, boss, I do think they should be easy to beat. After all, they're so "
"small, almost as small as us."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 843
msgid ""
"You idiot! Can't you see it's taking much too long to overcome them? Forget "
"it! It's time to bring in the big guys."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Goblin Handler Jabb
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 848
msgid "Ok, boss."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 854
msgid ""
"This is tougher than I thought. I don't care what my arrogant handler said "
"before - call in the heavy cavalry!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Greedy Farmer
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 870
msgid "We've had enough. Let's go home, boys!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Greedy Villager
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 878
msgid "Fall back, lads! Let the big guns take care of it."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Evil Goblin Trader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 892
msgid ""
"How can this be? And that summer villa for me to retire in was just one "
"sales trip away..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 896
msgid ""
"Against all odds, the boss of the goblin traders has been slain. And yet, "
"the others still persevered and finally overcame the proud young douche..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 905
msgid ""
"Ha! The dragon may have taken me after all, but its head has been cut off "
"just the same. Never will my own head drop in disgrace like this."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/1_Led_Astray.cfg, line: 925
msgid ""
"Jacques has persevered for five days, and still he stands high upon a pile "
"of slain adversaries. Finally, at long last, they manage to overcome him. "
"Fear is in their eyes, but they still glisten in anticipation of the gold "
"coins that such a sturdy fighter will fetch in the Wild Plains..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=2_Captivity
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 3
msgid "Captivity"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 10
msgid ""
"Jacques was taken to one of the ships of the traders waiting in the nearby "
"deeper waters. A treasure ship, indeed! It was Jacques himself that was the "
"treasure, and he could only wonder what the Goblin traders had in store for "
"him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 14
msgid ""
"He was taken below deck, to a cramped little cell, filled with other "
"captives of all shapes and sizes. There were humans, no doubt tricked "
"unawares like himself, but also several other races: sturdy little dwarves, "
"pointy-eared elves, even merfolk that Jacques only ever saw in his dreams."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 18
msgid ""
"On another day, he would consider this to be his dreams coming true. But not "
"on that day, and not in the following weeks that he spent being seasick and "
"homesick as the ship cut through the waves on its journey, day in and day "
"out. Every now and then, a few of the captives would be taken away, and "
"occasionally others would join the unfortunate crowd."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 21
msgid ""
"Finally, his turn came. Weakened from the long journey, he was taken ashore "
"in a wondrous land, which to eyes unaccustomed to light seemed full of "
"glistening golden sparkle. Jacques felt his spirits lifting as soon as he "
"stepped on hard soil, but they sank again when, a few hours of tedious "
"marching later, he and a few of his newfound friends were led into a cave "
"and left open air behind them once more."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 24
msgid ""
"Once underground, they walked on for what seemed like an eternity. Jacques "
"started thinking that he would never see the light of day again. Still, a "
"wondrous sight opened up to the captives as they were finally pushed into "
"what seemed like a grand chamber."
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Thief
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 45
msgid "Dishevelled Jacques"
msgstr ""
#
#. [unit]: type=Spearman, id=George
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 59
msgid "George"
msgstr ""
#
#. [unit]: type=Saurian Augur, id=Paula
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 73
msgid "Paula"
msgstr ""
#
#. [unit]: type=Orcish Grunt, id=Carl
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 87
msgid "Carl"
msgstr ""
#
#. [unit]: type=Elvish Archer, id=Almain
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 101
msgid "Almain"
msgstr ""
#
#. [unit]: type=Lieutenant, id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 143
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 278
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 78
msgid "Lieutenant Popper"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]
#. [side]: type=Gryphon, id=Hatrox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 188
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 108
msgid "Wild Beasts"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 196
msgid "Defeat the beasts."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=lose
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 200
msgid "Death of Jacques or end of turns."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 214
msgid ""
"It is a strange chamber - Jacques is certain that they are very deep, and "
"pools of lava seem to confirm it. And yet, the chamber is also filled with "
"exotic plants and two pools of water. There is no doubt that these are some "
"strange lands... or strange people... or both."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 219
msgid ""
"Jacques is ushered in with four other newcomers, all of them seemingly as "
"lost as he is. Before them, at some distance, they can see three thrones, "
"although only two are occupied. Closer to them, they see a heavily armed man "
"who observes them, bemused."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 224
msgid "An odd lot we have got again, wouldn't you say Your Highness?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 228
msgid "As long as they do their job, Popper, as long as they do their job."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 232
msgid ""
"Of course, Your Highness. Now, allow me to offer a few welcoming words to "
"the newcomers."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 236
msgid ""
"Welcome to the Wild Plains! As everything in life, you are here to serve a "
"purpose. And this purpose is to make sure that the workers on the outside "
"are safe from the beasts that would otherwise roam the plains."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 240
msgid ""
"Now, you do not need to know the ins and outs of why you are chosen to do "
"this or why it even needs to be done in the first place. The only important "
"thing to know is what you will be facing. Now, two of the most common "
"types..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 270
msgid "Ahh, a picture is worth a thousand words, wouldn't you say?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 274
msgid ""
"Argh! Ruphulus, I don't think that was the best idea. Well, I suppose this "
"will be your first little test. Help us get rid of them, quick! And try not "
"to get killed!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 289
msgid "A shame indeed, he seemed to show promise, this young lad."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 300
msgid ""
"Not getting rid of all the beasts in time, Jacques is suspected of either "
"being incapable or liking them too much to do the job he would be asked to "
"do. Thus, he is stripped of his hunter duties and taken to the mines "
"instead, left there to rotten until the end of his days..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 315
msgid "I'm getting killed! Quick, Ruphulus, get me out of here!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 328
msgid "Hahahaha! Having fun yet?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 348
msgid "Die, beast!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 367
msgid "Two down, two more to go!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 386
msgid "Only one more left!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 405
msgid "We did it!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 409
msgid "Hahahaha, well done, kids."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 413
msgid ""
"Ruphulus, your sense of humor is quite... astounding. Please do not bring "
"these creatures into our halls anymore."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 417
msgid "But of course, Your Majesty. Your wish is my command, without a doubt."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 422
msgid ""
"OK, enough *fun* for one day, I reckon. Newcomers, you will be escorted to "
"your quarters. Get as much rest as you can, for tomorrow morning your work "
"will commence."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg, line: 426
msgid ""
"And you, men, clean up this mess. What do I want? The floors polished clean. "
"When do I want it? Now!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=3_Hard_Labour
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 3
msgid "Hard Labour"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 9
msgid ""
"Jacques was led to his lodging which turned out not to be too bad. The bed "
"was comfortable, or so at least it felt, without the nausea of the constant "
"swaying that he had to endure during the ship's voyage."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 12
msgid ""
"He wondered about what befell him, and whether it might still turn out for "
"the better in the end. It was not as bad as he feared - the lodgings were "
"half-decent and the job he was supposed to do was not impossible. Yes, one "
"could die, but there were fates much worse than that."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 15
msgid ""
"Come to think of it, it wasn't entirely clear why his captors needed him and "
"other captives to take care of the killings of the beasts. They seemed quite "
"capable in general, his captors, including the wonderful feat of having the "
"outside world replicated in a deep cave."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 18
msgid ""
"Jacques knew that there was something else about these underground caverns "
"that struck him during the fight, but he couldn't quite remember what it "
"was. And, straining to remember it, he slowly drifted away to sleep..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 21
msgid ""
"... until he was woken early in the morning. It wasn't even sunrise yet as "
"he was rushed to dress and join a group of captives, waiting to go outside."
msgstr ""
#
#. [modify_unit]
#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Thief
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 41
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 152
msgid "Bewildered Jacques"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: type=Orcish Leader, id=Gronar
#. [unit]: id=Gronar, type=Orcish Leader
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 60
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 80
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 42
msgid "Gronar"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: type=Gryphon, id=Hatrox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 88
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 57
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 74
msgid "Hatrox"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 116
msgid "Defeat ten beasts before the turns run out."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=lose
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 120
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 122
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 445
msgid "Turns run out or Jacques gets killed."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 164
msgid ""
"As Jacques and his friends come out of the cave entrance (one of many, he "
"assumes), the sun is about to come up. The captors bid them farewell and "
"quickly go back inside, as if they were afraid of the beasts that lurk in "
"the plains around them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 169
msgid ""
"As for the plains, it is now clearer to him why the land appeared to be "
"covered in golden sparkle the day before - they are in a desert. The terrain "
"is unfamiliar to him and he does not have a solid grasp of his surroundings, "
"but he can just make out the hills at the edge of the horizon in one "
"direction."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 174
msgid ""
"His gaze is noticed by the man leaning against a rocky wall who seems to be "
"leading the hunting party today - an orcish brute by the name of Gronar who "
"speaks up."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 179
msgid ""
"Another day awaits us, fellows! Most of you know what to do; as for the "
"newcomers, you follow us at the back and try to learn fast. And watch out "
"for nasty surprises! Out here, the penalty for ignorance is quite severe."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 183
msgid ""
"Oh, and one more thing for those new to this - do not even think of making a "
"run for it. Apart from those impassable mountains in front of us, there is "
"nothing but miles and miles of desert all around us. So, if you escape, the "
"desert will kill you - if, that is, the Shadowhounds don't get to you first."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 187
msgid ""
"But what about the sea, sir? It was a relatively short trip for me to get "
"here, yesterday. Surely it must be near."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 192
msgid ""
"Yes, it is, Bambi. Why, it's just on the other side of those mountain peaks "
"over there. Shame that they are impassable. So, unless you manage to find a "
"way to fly or ask King Bombasan to lead you through the underground caverns, "
"forget it, you ain't going home!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 196
msgid ""
"But enough chit-chat! Onwards, hunters, and bring me pelts, tails and fangs!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 207
msgid ""
"Arrgh, that surely woke them up! Look, they're crawling out of their holes! "
"Brace yourself, everybody!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [print]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 248
msgid "$count beasts defeated."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 261
msgid ""
"Shouldn't this be enough for one day? Let's get back inside before more of "
"them come out."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 265
msgid ""
"Having done their daily chore, the captives slowly make their way back "
"towards the safety of their underground prison. Jacques is dead tired, but "
"also invigorated with a fresh sense of purpose. He is still alive. He will "
"NOT rot to death in this prison. And he WILL, somehow, find a way out."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 284
msgid ""
"Argh, they got me! But do not lose hope, comrades! Fight on and victory will "
"be yours..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 302
msgid ""
"As the survivors rest by the cave entrance, Jacques receives an additional "
"surge of high spirits as he witnesses an unexpected sight. A figure slowly "
"approaches, dragging itself across the sand - it is Gronar, somehow "
"surviving the onslaught of the beasts and making it back, albeit greatly "
"wounded."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 309
msgid ""
"As the survivors approach the cave entrance, suddenly a wolf appears out of "
"nowhere and makes a lunge for Jacques. Jacques freezes in fear, but at the "
"last moment another figure jumps in front of him and intercepts wolf's "
"attack, then hacks the beast in half. It is Gronar, taking a deep wound "
"himself but saving Jacques' life."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 323
msgid ""
"Obviously in possession of more bravery than cunning, Jacques plunges into a "
"struggle with a beast too rashly. He goes for the kill but sees his feet "
"swept away from under him. Suddenly, the beasts are all over him, and then "
"darkness embraces him as he lays dead on the ground. The other hunters look "
"at him impassively and move on, leaving yet another body to be devoured by "
"the beasts and the sand..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/3_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 335
msgid ""
"Not being able to complete the task swiftly, Jacques and his fellow hunters "
"are suddenly swarmed by scorpions coming at them from all sides. They fight "
"valiantly, but finally succumb to the sheer might of numbers, and Jacques is "
"no more."
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 3
msgid "Unrest in the Ranks"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 9
msgid ""
"The time spent on the outside made Jacques dead tired, and yet he felt both "
"his courage and strength rising as the captives returned to their lodgings. "
"Still, what he craved most was his bed and he was on the verge of falling "
"asleep when yelling woke him up..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [modify_unit]
#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Thief
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 29
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 94
msgid "Tired Jacques"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: type=Bandit, id=Pollox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 55
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 70
msgid "Pollox"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 78
msgid "Defeat Pollox or resist until the end of turns."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 102
msgid ""
"Jacques rushes out to see Gronar and a bandit quarreling in the communal "
"area of the lodgings. Gronar, still aching from the wounds he got on the "
"outside, is standing against the edge of the plants and the fountain "
"adorning even the most barren of underground caverns, and the bandit "
"towering over him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Pollox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 107
msgid ""
"You are not fit to lead us, Gronar. You are as weak on the inside as you are "
"on the outside!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 111
msgid ""
"I'm sorry you feel like that, Pollox, but you don't know what you're saying."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Pollox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 115
msgid ""
"We should have rebelled against these stupid cave dwellers long ago! "
"Instead, you keep leading us into the wretched desert to be slaughtered week "
"in and week out."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Gronar
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 119
msgid "Now, be sensible, Pollox. There is no way we can stand up to..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Pollox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 123
msgid ""
"No! You have followed their sun-hating ways for too long and are too blind "
"to see the light yourself. I think it is time for new leadership among the "
"oppressed."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 130
msgid ""
"Jacques sees Pollock's arm move at a blurry speed and connect with Gronar's "
"head. For a few seconds, all that is heard around the cavern is the echo of "
"that one hit. Then, Gronar's body slowly collapses to the ground..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 139
msgid "NOOOO! Gronar, noooo!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Pollox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 143
msgid "What are you complaining about, little brat? Do you want to join him?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 147
msgid "You will be the one joining him, you murderer!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 151
msgid "Some men speak up to support Jacques. Others side with Pollox."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Pollox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 156
msgid "Ah, every place has a few rats that need to be exterminated."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 236
msgid "Hahaha! The little brat has gone to join his beloved mentor again."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Pollox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 259
msgid "Damn you, you cowards! May you rot in this godforsaken place forever!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 263
msgid "At least the company will be better than where you're going."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 286
msgid "What has been going on in here?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 290
msgid "I... I can't quite say."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 294
msgid "What do you mean, you can't say? I demand to know!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 298
msgid ""
"It was Pollox and his men. It was as if they were... poisoned, somehow. But "
"I can't understand it."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 302
msgid ""
"Poisoned, you say? But not like... a remote physical reaction to something?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 306
msgid ""
"No, I mean... I don't quite know what I mean. It was as if something had "
"poisoned their mind."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 310
msgid ""
"Hmmm, I see. Men, take the remaining attackers into the dungeon! As for the "
"rest of you, get a good night's sleep, for tomorrow a big task awaits you."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 314
msgid ""
"As Popper and his guard depart with the remaining culprits, Jacques returns "
"to the fallen body of Gronar. He has hardly known the orc and yet he feels a "
"pang of sadness as he looks at the former captive leader. Then, he spots his "
"bow on the ground. Whether it is out of a habitual thief's impulse or out of "
"respect for Gronar, he picks it up. It is a good bow. Would he know how to "
"use it?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 319
msgid ""
"As he returns to his bed, still clutching the bow, Jacques finds new "
"resolve. He would not despair. Tomorrow would be another day, and tonight he "
"would start preparing for it by taking a good night's sleep."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/4_Unrest_in_the_Ranks.cfg, line: 324
msgid ""
"And that was it! He remembers what has been bothering him ever since he "
"first entered the caverns. Somehow, even this deep, his captors have managed "
"to create the atmosphere of the planet's surface, including the time of day "
"from dusk till dawn; all of it, that is, but the height of the daytime. If "
"they had managed to fool the laws of physics, why omit the true light of day?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=5_More_Hard_Labour
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 3
msgid "More Hard Labour"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 9
msgid ""
"The next morning, at the beginning, seemed a repetition of the first mission "
"on the outside. Again, the hunting captives assembled before dawn and made "
"their way to the outside. And yet, it soon became evident that this time "
"things would be different."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 12
msgid ""
"For one thing, Jacques was put at the helm of the expedition. He was to have "
"command of the forces already at his disposal, and a few more might be made "
"available in a day or two."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 15
msgid ""
"But even more importantly, there was to be a change in tactics. His captors "
"came to the conclusion that merely picking away at a stray beast here or "
"there would hardly make the desert any safer in the long run. So, it was "
"decided to strike at the heart of the beast horde. Or, rather, the two "
"hearts."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 18
msgid ""
"For, while they couldn't furnish him with clearer information, the captors "
"told him that much: there were two beasts that pushed and ruled their kind. "
"Strike at them and the beast menace might disappear. Such, accordingly, were "
"Jacques' orders - kill them both or perish trying."
msgstr ""
#
#. [event]
#. [modify_unit]
#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Sand Trapper
#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Thief
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 38
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 131
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 163
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 178
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 198
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 33
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 63
msgid "Determined Jacques"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: id=Scorpion Queen, type=Giant Scorpion
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 80
msgid "Scorpion Queen"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: id=Scorpion Queen, type=Giant Scorpion
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 98
msgid "Scorpions"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 118
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 441
msgid "Defeat the two enemy leaders."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 156
msgid ""
"As Jacques leaves the cave and sets up a base from which to organize his "
"troops, he thinks for a moment on what is happening to him. Killing beasts "
"in the desert for survival is a long way away from harassing drunks and old "
"ladies, and his roguish days are starting to look like a thing of the past. "
"He is determined he should also learn how to use his newly acquired bow."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 184
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 204
msgid ""
"As Jacques leaves the cave and sets up a base from which to organize his "
"troops, he thinks for a moment on what is happening to him. He realizes that "
"the great changes he's experienced in his life have caused him to change. He "
"has left his roguish ways behind him. He also finds that he is a better shot "
"with a bow than he imagined."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 213
msgid ""
"But he decides to reflect further on all that later. His first priority is "
"to find the two beast leaders and kill them, and to do so without losing too "
"many of his charges."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 218
msgid ""
"Remember everybody, search for any clues that might lead us to where the "
"leaders are hiding, but be careful about the nasty surprises they might "
"spring on us along the way!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 247
msgid ""
"Look at that oasis, we may go here to heal our bruises and quench our "
"thirst. But it's strange to see water, grass and a tree, on that sea of sand."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 288
msgid "Who goes there? Friend or foe?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 292
msgid "It talks!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 296
msgid "Friend or foe? Be warned, laddie, I shall not ask again!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 300
msgid "Err, friend, I suppose. Who are you? And what are you doing here?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 305
msgid ""
"Harrumph! Friend, it says. Although, if it speaks, it canna be one of the "
"beasts. Unless it belongs to the old rascal, of course."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 309
msgid ""
"Of course we are not of the beasts! Why, we are fighting them, albeit not as "
"much for our own sake as for the sake of our captors. We have to find and "
"kill the two leaders, can you help?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 314
msgid ""
"Arrr, interesting, if I do say so meself. It is rarely that I see a company "
"come out so far from the cave. Very rarely, indeed! Why, the last time was "
"when Kyoko first got here."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 318
msgid "Kyoko?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 322
msgid ""
"Well, Princess Kyoko, I reckon I should've said. I must add, I would've "
"expected King Bombasan to send a rescue party sooner, you know!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 326
msgid "Princess Kyoko?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 330
msgid ""
"She is very ill, as I'm sure you can imagine. Why, all that sunshine got to "
"her, and she is quite badly done in. We have been doing our best to keep her "
"safe and alive, but I must say you showed up in the nick of time. She needs "
"help and medicine, and she needs them fast."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 370
msgid ""
"The woses spread their branches and you spot a woman lying on the ground "
"between them. A beautiful woman, and yet clearly in a lot of pain."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 375
msgid "She is the daughter of King Bombasan?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 379
msgid ""
"Hah! You do not know? Don't they think she might still be alive? Surely, the "
"old geezer could not avoid the King making inquiries? Harrumph! It seems we "
"really need to talk."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 383
msgid ""
"Suddenly, the body of the Princess stirs and she lifts herself up. She has "
"obviously been listening to the conversation, and struggles to speak."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 388
msgid ""
"What? Is it true? My father knows nothing of me being left here in the open?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 392
msgid ""
"Rest, dear girl, rest, don't strain yourself. But there is no time to waste. "
"Jacques, I agree that you should first do away with the two leaders of the "
"beastly menace, and then, in moderate safety, we shall talk."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 396
msgid "I shall try to do so, for the sake of the Princess as well as our own."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 400
msgid ""
"I will let my offspring join you to help protect the Princess or fight the "
"beasts. But first things first - have you found the Scorpion Queen yet?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 404
msgid "I'm afraid not."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 408
msgid ""
"Ahh, she hides well, the old bat. If you go straight south from here, you "
"should find a hill of rubble. It used to be an outpost of the cave dwellers, "
"before that affliction to the sun locked them inside their caves. Now, it "
"serves as the domain of the Scorpion Queen."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 412
msgid ""
"Go there and look for the secret entrance next to the biggest rock. But be "
"careful! She will not be alone!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 416
msgid ""
"And then, once you defeat her, come back and I will try to help you with the "
"Griffin Lord, if you still need me to. In fact, you might want to stay away "
"from the mountains until I do."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 427
msgid ""
"The Griffin Lord is no more! It was incredibly hard, yet we persevered and "
"overcame him and his minions. But the Scorpion Queen still needs to be "
"taken, and your advice will be most helpful."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 433
msgid "Thank you and see you soon, I hope."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=lose
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 449
msgid "Death of Princess Kyoko."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 481
msgid ""
"As they start searching around the biggest rock in the rubble as Arbor "
"suggested, suddenly they hear a loud hiss. Bewildered, everybody steps back "
"as the Scorpion Queen and her guard appear before them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 506
msgid "Let's get her!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 528
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 635
msgid ""
"We did it! We killed the two leaders! Now, quick, let us return to the "
"talking tree and get to the bottom of this Princess Kyoko business."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 539
msgid ""
"We did it! I hope we will no longer see new scorpions springing up on us "
"from their holes. Now let us quickly return to the talking tree and ask for "
"help with the other leader!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 574
msgid ""
"Hah! You did it, young lad. Excellent news, but the other leader is stronger "
"still, and even more difficult to get to."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 578
msgid ""
"As you may well know, he resides atop that mountain range over there, nested "
"in between the impassable peaks. As things stand, the only accessible path "
"leading to him is very narrow and it may take ages to overcome the beasts "
"guarding him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 582
msgid ""
"However, this old tree has learned a thing or two in its time, and may just "
"be able to help. Now, if I focus the ancient tree power of spring on a few "
"of those impassable peaks, I just might change their climate well enough to "
"make them slightly less impassable..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 603
msgid ""
"As the elder wose strains its branches in concentration, Jacques sees that "
"some of the impassable peaks have indeed become passable. Now, getting to "
"the Gryphon Lord should be easier."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 608
msgid "Come back when you're done. As I said, we need to talk. Now, good luck!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Hatrox
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 624
msgid ""
"Curse you, you little scum! The old hag was right, you are more of a "
"challenge than your puny features betray. Still, I am certain that I will be "
"avenged."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 646
msgid ""
"We did it! We killed the first leader! Now onwards, let us send the other "
"one to join him!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 661
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 679
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 696
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 714
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 731
msgid "Watch out, another wave has appeared!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 784
msgid ""
"They all tried to protect the Princess, but one of the beasts managed to "
"sneak past the defenses and strike at her lying body. Immediately, the "
"nearest guard was upon the beast and it was slain, and yet it was too late, "
"for one hit was all it took to take the life of the Princess. And without "
"her to aid him, Jacques' fate would not change."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 799
msgid ""
"It was said afterwards that a big black bird circled above Jacques and "
"started cackling as he was dealt a deadly blow by the beast. His troops "
"fought valiantly on, but without clear direction stood no chance against the "
"onslaught of the beasts..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 818
msgid ""
"As Jacques fights the beasts and tries to prevent them from hurting all "
"those under his command, he realizes that the great changes he's experienced "
"in his life have caused him to change. He has truly left his roguish ways "
"behind him. He lifts Gronar's bow up high and leads his troops onwards."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/5_More_Hard_Labour.cfg, line: 835
msgid ""
"Not being able to complete the task swiftly, Jacques and his fellow hunters "
"are suddenly swarmed by beasts coming at them from all sides. They fight "
"valiantly, but finally succumb to the sheer might of numbers, and Jacques is "
"no more."
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=6_Seeing_the_Light
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 3
msgid "Seeing the Light"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 9
msgid ""
"With the leaders of the beasts slain, a quiet calm has suddenly come over "
"the dunes."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 12
msgid ""
"Jacques and his friends slowly made their way back to the oasis, where they "
"found Arbor tending to the fragile Princess Kyoko. Jacques looked at the "
"Princess and couldn't help noticing that she was very beautiful. From what "
"he saw of King Bombasan, it was hard to imagine that she could, indeed, be "
"his daughter."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 15
msgid ""
"Looking at her, what he wanted above all was to protect her and make sure "
"she was okay. The elder wose noticed the young man's concern and betrayed an "
"imperceptible smile. In his lifetime, he had seen this same tale weave "
"itself a thousand times: when it came to the game of love, the young such as "
"Kyoko and Jacques were often just pawns at the mercy of the inevitable fate."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 18
msgid ""
"Arbor lulled Princess Kyoko to sleep and laid her gently on the ground. Then "
"he motioned for Jacques to come near. It was time to finally have that talk."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 71
msgid ""
"I'm certain you have many questions, Jacques, but I can only provide answers "
"to some of them. I will start by saying what I know for certain, if that's "
"all right by you."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 75
msgid "Anything might help, so please take your time."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 79
msgid ""
"The cave-dwelling people are a mix of different races just as much as you "
"lot are, as I'm sure you've noticed by now. You see, in the bygone days they "
"lived on the coast beyond those mountains and, as it is with most coastal "
"people, their gene pool benefited from the constant flow of the ships "
"passing these lands."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 83
msgid ""
"But, beneficial though this genetic mix was, it seems they somehow didn't "
"take well to the hot sun. First their skin would suffer, then they would get "
"physically ill whenever they stayed out in the sun too long. They built "
"dwellings in that cave system you've seen, and took to spending ever longer "
"periods of time inside."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 87
msgid ""
"Now, one thing they had to their advantage, or so it seemed, was a powerful "
"mage that came to live with them. He has been with these people for as long "
"as I can remember, and that says a lot. Come to think of it, he must carry "
"his years extremely well, seeing that he is still around."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 91
msgid "Ruphulus."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 95
msgid ""
"Aye, Ruphulus. Now he had - as he doubtlessly still does - a remarkable "
"ability, this Ruphulus did. He could create the impression of the outside "
"ambiance even in the darkest of caves. And he did just that, so that it "
"seemed to the people living in the caves as if they were still living on the "
"outside - except for the brightest parts of the day, of course."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 99
msgid ""
"That explains why I felt it, too, when I was in the caves. But they also "
"have fresh pools of water and plants in the caves! How do they manage to "
"grow plants without the necessary light?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 103
msgid ""
"That, I'm afraid, I do not know. This mage has many powers, and that surely "
"must be one of them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 107
msgid ""
"Yes, he is a powerful mage. When we were first taken to the caves, he made "
"beasts appear out of thin air!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 111
msgid ""
"Which leads us to the penultimate part of what I have to say. I am not "
"entirely clear about it all, but this mage appears to have much to do with "
"the condition that the cave dwellers - and you, for that matter - have found "
"themselves in. I suspect he might have had something to do with the people "
"getting  afflicted by the sun. And, as Kyoko kindly explained to me, it was "
"him who urged King Bombasan to start trading with the goblin traders and "
"acquire captives to fight the beasts in the desert. Why, I do not know, but "
"it seems odd, even if fear of the sun might be incentive enough."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 115
msgid ""
"So is that why Kyoko is so ill? Because she has been exposed to the sun for "
"so long?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 119
msgid ""
"In part yes. But it was Ruphulus' doing which really brought her to this. "
"He..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 123
msgid "Arbor, perhaps I could explain this part?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 127
msgid ""
"My dear girl, you woke up! You know you shouldn't exert yourself, you need "
"all the rest you can get."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 131
msgid ""
"I know, Arbor, but this girl is way past being girlie. Besides, with the sun "
"setting down for the day, I'm sure my condition cannot get any worse."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 135
msgid "Milady, I put myself at your disposal."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 139
msgid ""
"Disposable though you are, brute, you have proven your worth today. For "
"that, I will ask my father to show clemency in your regard."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 143
msgid ""
"That is a matter that certainly needs to be addressed in due time, and "
"perhaps not quite on those terms. But more urgently, why are you here? And "
"what was Ruphulus' doing in that?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 147
msgid "That old swine is a traitor!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 151
msgid ""
"Jacques is taken aback. Not by the fact that Ruphulus is a traitor, of "
"course - by now, that much should be quite evident even to a child. Rather, "
"what surprises him is that Kyoko is not very graceful, with a curt mouth and "
"a somewhat denigrating attitude towards him. She is not a princess who "
"lovingly gazes at her rescuer. No, in fact, she is quite annoying."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 156
msgid ""
"He has always been scheming away at something in his own private halls, "
"which also have a secret passage that leads to further unexplored caves "
"beyond. I wouldn't even know of it if he hadn't lured me to his rooms on "
"some stupid pretext and then proceeded to make a pass at me. Untold riches "
"awaited me behind the secret door, he said, if only I agreed to join him in "
"whatever it was he wanted to do."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 160
msgid ""
"I kicked him where it hurts and left, thinking that was that. He did, "
"indeed, stay away from me since then - until I caught him a few months ago, "
"trying to pour something into my father's soup. I knew right away that it "
"meant nothing good, so I screamed and ran at him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 164
msgid ""
"I knocked the bowl over, but then he got hold of me and hit me so hard that "
"I nearly lost consciousness. I have a vague recollection of some liquid "
"being forced down my throat, and being dragged somewhere. Then, there were "
"wings around me, and suddenly I was flying... and then I was falling, and "
"then it all went dark..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 168
msgid ""
"Ruphulus must have somehow taken her to a place where he could hand her over "
"to Hatrox, the Griffin Lord, who took her to the mountains, but by a spell "
"of good fortune dropped her near an oasis. One of my children found her in "
"the brush, nearly dead, partly from the fall and partly from the poison that "
"she must have been given from the spilt bowl. It was fortunate that we found "
"her when we did, another day in the sun and she would be gone."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 172
msgid ""
"That bastard left me to die in the desert, and he's scheming to kill my "
"father. We need to get him!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 176
msgid ""
"You certainly must. But before you do, you all must rest. My children and I "
"will make sure that no one, including the sun, disturbs you tonight and over "
"the course of the day tomorrow. Then, at dusk tomorrow, you will be able to "
"start making your way back to the caves. That way you will reach them before "
"sunrise and will still be relatively rested when you confront Ruphulus."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 180
msgid ""
"That we shall do indeed, confront him and send him to oblivion! But won't "
"you be joining us, Arbor?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Arbor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/6_Seeing_the_Light.cfg, line: 184
msgid ""
"Alas, even trees get old one day, and my old branches can no longer move "
"around as they used to. No, I will have to stay here, but I will be with you "
"in spirit. Now rest, children, and may you have happy dreams."
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=7_Confronting_the_Traitor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 3
msgid "Confronting the Traitor"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 10
msgid ""
"That night, Jacques indeed had a dream, but it was a most peculiar one. He "
"dreamt that he had returned to his home village of Mosh. But he was not the "
"thief that had only recently left those shores, nor even a trapper. No, he "
"was a king, and people cowered in fear at the mere sight of him. Was he a "
"monster in their eyes? Was his face bursting with vengeance? And where was "
"his family, where was his father?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 13
msgid ""
"Kyoko also had a dream. She dreamt she was a fly, buzzing around Ruphulus. "
"He would try to swat her but she evaded him, blow after blow, and thus it "
"went on for ages. Finally, she stopped and landed on the mage's knee, and "
"Ruphulus broke a wide grin. His hand moved to deal the final blow, "
"accompanied by his maniacal laughter. But then, laughter turned into a "
"scream..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 16
msgid ""
"As Kyoko finally opened her eyes, she realized Jacques was shaking her "
"awake. He wanted to know what had made her scream, but she couldn't tell "
"him. After all, she didn't even know what it meant herself. So she brushed "
"him aside and set about preparing for the long march. The sun was about to "
"set and it would soon be time to get going."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 19
msgid ""
"The little group bade farewell to Arbor and headed for the caves. Jacques "
"was sad to part ways with such a formidable friend, but he was also "
"determined to see this through. He led his people safely across the desert, "
"encountering only one giant scorpion along the way."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 22
msgid ""
"As they reached the entrance into the cave system, the guards cried out in "
"bewilderment: the Princess was alive! The news spread quickly, and loud "
"cheers were soon heard from various directions. As for Kyoko, she was home "
"and her slightly improved complexion showed it. She ran for the grand "
"chamber so fast that Jacques and his men could barely keep up..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [modify_unit]
#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Sand Trapper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 37
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 166
msgid "Angry Jacques"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 121
msgid "Defeat Ruphulus and his beasts."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=lose
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 125
msgid "Death of Jacques, Kyoko or King Bombasan."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=lose
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 129
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 128
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 465
msgid "Turns run out."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 264
msgid ""
"As Kyoko, Jacques and the others burst into the grand chamber, the guards at "
"first reach for the weapons, then recognize the Princess and bow their heads "
"in greeting. King Bombasan throws his hands up in the air and shouts out in "
"joy. But, disturbingly, Jacques sees even Ruphulus explode into a wide grin."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 269
msgid ""
"My dear Kyoko is alive? Alive and well? Oh, what joy! Oh, what happiness!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 273
msgid ""
"Happiness indeed, Your Highness. Welcome home, our beloved Princess. I trust "
"all is well?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 277
msgid ""
"Father! Ruphulus is a snake that we cherished in our bosom! He's a traitor!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 281
msgid ""
"What do you mean, sweet child? Are you sure? Has the sun perhaps played "
"tricks on your mind?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 285
msgid ""
"No, she is right! Ruphulus is behind most if not all of the misfortunes that "
"have befallen you."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 289
msgid ""
"Silence! You are not to speak in front of His Majesty without special leave "
"to do so!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 293
msgid ""
"Let him speak, Popper! And have your men apprehend Ruphulus before he gets "
"away, so that we can try him!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Lieutenant Popper
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 297
msgid "Your Majesty? What should I do?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 301
msgid ""
"Hahahaha! You always were a dimwit, Popper. Here, I'll tell you what to do. "
"Die!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 345
msgid ""
"With a particularly well aimed bolt, Lieutenant Popper crumples to the "
"floor. No sooner does his body hit the ground, however, then Ruphulus is "
"already over it, and he begins drinking the freshly spilt blood."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 352
msgid "What are you doing, you beast?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 375
msgid ""
"Finally, you talk sense, you old fool, for a beast, a magnificent beast is "
"what I am! See me in my complete glory and cower in fear!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 379
msgid ""
"I may be an old fool, but you are older still! You'll never get away with "
"this! Guards, get him!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 384
msgid "Chaaarge!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 388
msgid "Come to me, my pets, come to me!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 421
msgid ""
"Ah yes! Forgive me, Your Majesty, as I know you hate unpleasant surprises, "
"but I must disappoint you again. These wonderful pools of water and plants "
"adorning your halls, as well as the ambiance of open nightly sky above you? "
"I'm afraid they have to go, as they're of no further use to me."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 429
msgid "My lovely chamber! What have we done to deserve this?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 466
msgid ""
"Against her better judgment and the dragon's warning, Kyoko takes a "
"desperate plunge for Ruphulus. And again, while growling with pure malice, "
"the dragon holds back."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 473
msgid ""
"As Kyoko takes a desperate plunge for Ruphulus and exchanges blows with him, "
"she realizes that he purposely tries not to hit her too hard. That is odd: "
"he would have his minions attack her and try to take her life, sure; but to "
"attack her directly - for some reason, that he does not want to do."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 513
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 609
msgid ""
"I've told you once before and I won't repeat myself again. I would prefer "
"not to stain my wings with your puny blood, so STAY AWAY!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 519
msgid ""
"Go play with my pets, Princess. And do not, I repeat, DO NOT come near me "
"again!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 562
msgid ""
"In the heat of the battle, as Ruphulus slashes, burns and stings about him, "
"he suddenly attacks Kyoko before she can get away. Kyoko is certain that "
"this time she is beyond hope, and yet, at the last instant the dragon again "
"tries to hold back."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 569
msgid ""
"In the heat of the battle, as Ruphulus slashes, burns and stings about him, "
"he suddenly attacks Kyoko. She braces and prepares for the worst - and yet, "
"astonishingly, at the very end the Dragon tries to hold back the strength of "
"his attack."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 615
msgid ""
"Your life is too weak for a dragon to take! Go give it to one of my pets, "
"and do not come near me again!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 638
msgid "Aaaargh! Mosh... father... K... Kyoko..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 652
msgid "Father, I'm sorry I... let... you... down."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 666
msgid ""
"With the King dead, all his forces as well as Kyoko lose the will to fight, "
"and they become an easy prey for the dragon."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 681
msgid "Ha! This is much easier than it was the first time round."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 700
msgid "It's true, feels like swatting flies!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 705
msgid "Brrrr! Must not think of swatting flies!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 715
msgid "Only one more of the nasty little pests left!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 725
msgid "The little pests are gone!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 746
msgid "Now let's focus all our strength on Ruphulus!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 759
msgid ""
"With every exchange of blows, the strength of Jacques and his comrades "
"diminishes and the strength of Ruphulus rises, until finally he overcomes "
"them completely, and darkness engulfs them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 774
msgid "Die, spawn of evil!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 778
msgid ""
"Hahahaha! Do you think your puny little swords and bows and whatnot can "
"really get me? Hahahaha!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Ruphulus
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 782
msgid ""
"You have tickled me well, I grant you that. But this will not finish here, "
"and not today!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 791
msgid ""
"In a puff of smoke, Ruphulus spreads his wings, rises from the ground and "
"passes through a secret opening in the ceiling that closes behind him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 816
msgid ""
"We will get him another day! Now let's focus all our strength on getting rid "
"of the beasts, and fast!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 833
msgid ""
"As Jacques fights the beasts and tries to prevent them from hurting all "
"those under his command, he realizes that the great changes he's experienced "
"in his life have caused him to change. He has truly left his roguish ways "
"behind you."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 846
msgid ""
"With the beasts slain and Ruphulus defeated, the survivors gasp for air. At "
"first, it seems as if it is just because of the battle fatigue. Soon, they "
"realize that the very air around them has become heavier; the magical "
"freshness that Ruphulus created has left with him."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 851
msgid ""
"King Bombasan runs to his daughter and embraces her. Then, he looks around "
"the newly barren chamber. With two valid reasons for emotion, it is no "
"wonder that a tear runs down his cheek."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 856
msgid ""
"I thank you from the bottom of my heart, Jacques, for bringing my daughter "
"back to me. I see now how foolish we were to be so easily manipulated by "
"Ruphulus, and I apologize for having so easily acquiesced to his pleadings "
"for slaves to defend us from the outside menace. Since he controlled the "
"beasts, I fear that this was somehow just another part of his plans to grow "
"in strength."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: type=Orcish Grunt
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 860
msgid ""
"Seeing how he drank blood out of Lieutenant Popper made me cringe, and "
"that's saying a lot for an Orc."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 864
msgid ""
"I also feel he influenced the captives, to have us meekly go to his regular "
"slaughters, when we could easily rebel or escape once we were outside. We "
"even believed that there were some dangerous creatures called Shadowhounds "
"in the desert beyond!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 868
msgid ""
"I'm sorry to say so, Jacques, but that much is true. There are indeed "
"Shadowhounds in the lands beyond, dangerous creatures that roam the dunes at "
"night and eat whatever is in their way. They descend upon you like a swarm "
"of locusts and start devouring your very life energy while you helplessly "
"watch."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 872
msgid "It sounds like these lands would best be avoided."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 876
msgid "And yet, it is precisely there that we must go."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 880
msgid ""
"What nonsense is this, my sweet child? You don't have to go anywhere! My "
"troops will protect us and with Jacques's help, should he wish to take "
"Popper's place as their commander, we should be quite safe."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 884
msgid "You're the one talking nonsense, dad!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 888
msgid ""
"(Good to see she hasn't lost any of her brusqueness, Jacques thinks to "
"himself.)"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 892
msgid ""
"I'm quite sure that Ruphulus has more secret openings that he can use to "
"enter and leave the caves as he pleases, and that his lair is right here, in "
"the unexplored deeper regions of the cave system that only he had access to. "
"I don't know what monstrous things he had been doing there all this time, "
"but I'm sure we won't like it."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 896
msgid "How can you be so sure?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 900
msgid ""
"Don't ask me how, but I am. And I fear that, any day now, we may have to "
"worry about attacks from both sides, from below as well as from above."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 913
msgid ""
"As if on cue, suddenly they hear the sound of war drums, coming from "
"somewhere far, far below them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 918
msgid ""
"You know as well as I do that getting the Book of Prophecies from the Temple "
"of Doomsday is our only chance of defeating that monster. And if we have to "
"go into the very heart of Shadowlands to get to it, so be it."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 922
msgid ""
"Listen to yourself, child! Temple of Doomsday, Book of Prophecies - it's "
"more likely the Book of Fairy Tales, if you ask me. These are but crazy "
"tales of old, and it won't do us much good if we start believing in them now."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 926
msgid ""
"But what else is there for us to do? The drums from below will keep getting "
"louder, and eventually closer and closer. To stay here means surely to "
"perish. To go to the Shadowlands means to have hope."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 930
msgid ""
"I have to agree with Kyoko. Surely we can do more than sit around and wait "
"for Ruphulus to come quench his thirst from our limp bodies. Look at the "
"barren chamber around us! This place has been doomed to die, and if we don't "
"do something about it, so shall we."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 934
msgid ""
"The King does not respond right away. He bows his head and spends a minute "
"in silent contemplation. Then he looks up with fresh determination in his "
"eyes."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=King Bombasan
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 939
msgid ""
"Perhaps I am indeed getting too old and cowardly. Okay, I give in, you "
"should go look for that stupid book. I would go with you, but my people need "
"me here; there are gates to be barred, defenses to be organized. Ruphulus "
"shall have a hard time getting his hands on these halls, and harder still "
"when you get back, book or no book!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg, line: 943
msgid ""
"And so it is that the next step is decided. Tired from the day's dramatic "
"events, all except the carefully placed sentries fall asleep, with the eerie "
"distant drum beat as their lullaby..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=8_The_Shadowlands
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 3
msgid "The Shadowlands"
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 11
msgid ""
"It is said that the Book of Prophecies contains and controls all that may or "
"may not happen, so that he who wields the Book of Prophecies wields the fate "
"of time. The book has not been seen for eons, and yet the rumor persists "
"that it exists, and that it is buried in the ruins of the Temple of "
"Doomsday, in the middle of what is now known as the Shadowlands."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 15
msgid ""
"The Temple of Doomsday, entrusted with the safekeeping of the Book, is said "
"to have once been a magnificent palace in the middle of a peaceful and "
"fertile valley, until some of the Bookkeepers attempted to usurp the Book "
"for their private worldly gains."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 19
msgid ""
"According to the legend, what ensued was a devastating struggle between the "
"loyal protectors of the Book and the usurpers, which ultimately led to the "
"destruction of the palace and the death of all within it. And yet, bound to "
"the book, they would persevere at the ruins in their shadowy forms, "
"devouring anyone who might dare to come near."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 23
msgid ""
"It is said that all of this was foretold in the Book, but that, once the "
"Book was lost in the struggle, nobody could read the prophecy and attempt to "
"amend it."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 26
msgid ""
"Not knowing if the stories were true, but without any alternative, in the "
"morning Jacques, Kyoko and a small party of soldiers set out on their quest. "
"They bid farewell to the King and his troops, who were already working hard "
"on strengthening the defenses of the halls, and headed for the Shadowlands."
msgstr ""
#
#. [part]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 29
msgid ""
"As a parting gift, King Bombasan gave Jacques a sword - it was the one that "
"belonged to Popper and was a finely crafted weapon. Jacques thanked the King "
"for the gift and decided he would use it as soon as he felt comfortable "
"wielding a longer blade."
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: type=Spectre, id=Night Guardian
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 66
msgid "Night Guardian"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: type=Ancient Lich, id=Lord Protector
#. [side]: type=Spectre, id=Night Guardian
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 81
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 110
msgid "Shadowhounds"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]: type=Ancient Lich, id=Lord Protector
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 95
msgid "Lord Protector"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 124
msgid "Find the Book of Prophecy."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 166
msgid ""
"As they make their way across the desert, Jacques is amazed at the fact that "
"he made it all this way while still clinging to all the external qualities "
"of a meager thief. If only he had acquired more experience in battle, he "
"could shed his chains of mediocrity and start becoming what he truly could "
"be."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 186
msgid ""
"As they make their way across the desert, Jacques realizes that he is being "
"called upon to acquire more and more duties. Pretty soon, the fate of "
"Kyoko's people may depend on his leadership abilities."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 213
msgid ""
"In the course of the journey, Jacques again feels the change of character "
"seeping through his bones. With the duties and responsibilities he has "
"undertaken, he is no regular hunter any more, but has become a true "
"commander to lead his troops into battle."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 218
msgid ""
"He swooshes Lieutenant Popper's sword through the air and decides he is "
"ready to use it in battle. He puts it next to Gronar's bow. His weaponry is "
"now a testament to two leaders that have already been smitten by this folly, "
"and he is determined not to be the third."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 227
msgid ""
"As they approach the Shadowlands, Kyoko cannot help but think of Ruphulus. "
"In her mind, she tries to revisit the day when she was taken from the caves. "
"It must have been his dragon wings that she remembers from that day. But "
"why, then, would he drop her so clumsily as to enable her to survive the "
"fall?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 238
msgid ""
"Besides, how could she forget that when they met in the heat of the battle, "
"he purposely decided to spare her life and even warned her to stay away from "
"him?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 245
msgid ""
"It was as if he couldn't kill her with his own hand. Why? It was this "
"nagging question, together with her dream from the night before, which made "
"her all the more determined to get the Book of Prophecies. Surely, that book "
"would have the answer."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 250
msgid ""
"As Kyoko shakes her mind clear, she realizes that they have already reached "
"the Shadowlands and are setting camp at the outskirts. The Temple of "
"Doomsday and the fort that surrounds it are already quite visible a short "
"distance away. Danger is nigh."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 255
msgid ""
"We are here. You can already spot the enemy within the fort. They are "
"currently still inside the walls, but as their time of day approaches, we "
"will soon see them come out to get at us. I suggest we form good offensive "
"lines and wait until dawn to engage them in battle."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 259
msgid ""
"Remember, our top priority is the Book of Prophecies. If anyone finds it, "
"call for help and guard it with your life. You're not doing it just for your "
"honor, you're doing it for the loved ones you've left back at the caves. May "
"heavens smile on us all!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 263
msgid ""
"For instance, there seem to be some buildings at the North side of the fort. "
"I suggest someone goes to investigate there before we engage the fiercest of "
"the enemies in vain."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 283
msgid ""
"As he fights the ghostly adversaries, Jacques realizes that his makeshift "
"soldiers boldly follow wherever he may lead them. In their eyes and his "
"heart, he is no longer a mere hunter but a true commander leading his troops "
"into battle."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 288
msgid ""
"He lifts Lieutenant Popper's sword high up in the air and calls out to "
"invigorate his troops, and they start fighting with renewed courage and "
"purpose."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 300
msgid ""
"As Jacques fights the beasts and tries to prevent them from hurting all "
"those under his command, he realizes that the great changes he's experienced "
"in his life have caused him to change. He has truly left his roguish ways "
"behind him. And yet, by that time even his newly acquired skills might not "
"be enough to truly lead his troops, so Jacques is aware he needs to advance "
"further still."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 328
msgid ""
"As they step into the house, Jacques hopes that they will find someone or "
"something useful inside. The house, however, is completely empty, with "
"nothing in it but the barest amenities."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 333
msgid ""
"However, as they turn to leave, suddenly they are accosted by a strange old "
"character."
msgstr ""
#
#. [unit]: type=Silver Mage, id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 341
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 732
msgid "Luxor"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 353
msgid ""
"Haha! I did not expect company so soon, and such an interesting one at that!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 357
msgid "Huh? Where did he come from?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 361
msgid ""
"Care for some tea? Cookies, perhaps? Not that I have either, but thought "
"it's good manners to ask. Luxor is the name, by the way."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 365
msgid "We apologize for disturbing you, sir, but we're in a bit of trouble."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 384
msgid ""
"You see, we came here on an urgent mission to find a special book, and have "
"encountered two armies of Shadowhounds on top of that. Now, we have "
"dispensed with the two Shadowhounds leaders, but the book is still nowhere "
"to be found."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 388
msgid "Ahh, but you didn't even make it to the actual temple, have you?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 392
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 427
msgid "Are you referring to that structure in the center of the fortress?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 396
msgid ""
"Of course I am, you genius you! Now, I suppose my magical barriers are still "
"intact, are they not? Well, now that the Shadowhounds are gone, I suppose I "
"may take them down."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 408
msgid "There, that should take care of that. And now, let's talk."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 419
msgid ""
"You see, we came here on an urgent mission to find a special item, and then "
"we have encountered two armies of Shadowhounds on top of that. Would you "
"happen to know where we could find this special... item, or at least be able "
"to help us fight the Shadowhounds?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 423
msgid ""
"Ahem... the book we could talk about, but perhaps we should first deal with "
"the pesky little ghosts, wouldn't you agree? Just to make sure, you didn't "
"yet make it to the Temple itself, have you?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 431
msgid ""
"Of course I am, you genius you! Now, I suppose that means my magical "
"barriers are still intact, are they? Excellent, for that may help you in "
"your fight."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 435
msgid ""
"You see, there is a special underground passage that allows one to go from "
"this insignificant cottage directly to the mighty Temple. But be careful, "
"it's one way only!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 439
msgid ""
"A special passage? I can see how that would be helpful to get our troops "
"into the center of the fortress. But the barriers would still be there, "
"wouldn't they?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 443
msgid ""
"At first, yes. But when you come out at the other end, you may wish to be "
"careful about the northernmost corner of the area. When you feel you have "
"gathered enough forces for the surprise attack from behind, examine that "
"spot and you will find the switch to make the barriers disappear."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 448
msgid ""
"Thank you, that will indeed be helpful. Would you perhaps wish to join us in "
"the fight?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 452
msgid ""
"Come to think of it, why not? Should be mighty fun, like the good old days..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 461
msgid "Defeat the two enemy leaders and find the Book of Prophecy."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 493
msgid ""
"Haha! I better get myself out of here, pronto, and lick my wounds somewhere "
"safe! See you later, folks!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 497
msgid ""
"With these words, Luxor disappears in a puff of smoke. Apparently, secret "
"passages are not the only way he can move around very quickly."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=unit
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 511
msgid "Found the switch and am pulling it!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 525
msgid "Now, let's go get them!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [unit]: type=Dwarvish Fighter, id=Choki
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 539
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 216
msgid "Choki"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Choki
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 546
msgid "Spare us, please!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 550
msgid "More enemies! And living ones, at that! Why should we spare you?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Choki
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 554
msgid ""
"We mean you no harm! We're just forced labor, kept here by the Shadowhounds "
"to do whatever tedious things they need doing. Mostly cleaning up after "
"their battles, these days, picking up bones of their unfortunate adversaries "
"and preparing them for shipment."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 558
msgid ""
"Shipment? Hmmm... We'll talk later. For now, if you don't like what you've "
"been forced to do, join us in the fight against your masters!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Choki
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 562
msgid ""
"Join you? Oh, we would, we would, but we're too afraid of our masters. We "
"have seen what they have done, and we dare not oppose them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 566
msgid "Ahh, so you would have us do your dirty work for you, will you?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Choki
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 570
msgid ""
"Forgive us, but the fear is too great. I'll tell you what, though - if you "
"manage to kill our masters, then we will join you. You have our word, and "
"the word of a dwarf is more dependable than steel."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 574
msgid "Fine, so be it! I will come back for you once this fight is over."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 605
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 650
msgid ""
"We did it! We killed the two leaders and the temple is secured. Now, let's "
"go meet with that crazy old mage and see what he has to say about the Book "
"of Prophecy."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 616
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 661
msgid ""
"We did it! We killed the two leaders and the temple is secured. But where is "
"the Book of Prophecy? We need to find the Book before we can rest!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 624
msgid ""
"The fierce Night Guardian is dead! Now, let's gather our powers and defeat "
"his Lord as well!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: id=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 669
msgid ""
"The formidable Lord Protector is dead! Now, let's gather our powers and "
"defeat his minion as well!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 682
msgid ""
"The Princess fought like a valiant fighter worthy of her dwarvish ancestry "
"and breezed through the enemy ranks worthy of her elven one. And yet, she "
"could not escape or overcome the adversary that struck her down..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 697
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 548
msgid ""
"It was said afterwards that a big black bird circled above Jacques and "
"started cackling as he was dealt a deadly blow by one of the Shadowhounds. "
"His troops fought valiantly on, but without clear direction stood no chance "
"against the onslaught of the hounds..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 709
msgid ""
"Not being able to complete the task swiftly, Jacques and his friends are "
"suddenly swarmed by Shadowhounds coming at them from all sides. They fight "
"valiantly, but finally succumb to the sheer might of numbers, and Jacques is "
"no more."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 754
msgid ""
"With the enemies defeated, Jacques and Kyoko are able to sit down with Luxor "
"and ask him about the Book of Prophecies."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 759
msgid ""
"Blimey, you showed them good, kids! Hahaha, I do feel sorry for the fools, "
"but I suppose they had it coming."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 763
msgid ""
"Who were they? Had they really once been the guardians of the Book of "
"Prophecies? And does the Book exist? And, if so, where is it?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 767
msgid ""
"Remember, laddie! Not all the legends you hear are true! But this one, "
"unfortunately, is. If it wasn't for that ambitious young mage and his "
"worldly greed, all of this might have been avoided..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 771
msgid ""
"So it is all true! I knew it! And the Shadowhounds were the usurpers, forced "
"to stay on as ghosts as eternal punishment."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 775
msgid ""
"Ahh, lassie, so young, so naive! You see, you have a lesson to learn about "
"life as well, and it is this: life isn't fair! The poor Shadowhounds you've "
"just defeated were not the usurpers, they were the honorable protectors of "
"the Book."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 779
msgid ""
"How can this be? They've been killing anyone who came near the Shadowlands, "
"and have been doing it for ages!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 783
msgid ""
"That they did, but I suppose it only seemed like protecting the Book in "
"their perverted minds. I can only imagine what turning into a shadow does to "
"one's mind."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 787
msgid "But if they weren't the rebels, who was?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 792
msgid ""
"Haha! T'was a young, foolish mage, called Luxor, I believe, who led them."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 796
msgid "You!?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 800
msgid ""
"See? I told you life wasn't fair. The honorable being forced to turn into "
"beasts by virtue of their pledge to protect the Book while the culprit is "
"left free."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 804
msgid "How did you stay alive? We thought everyone was killed in the struggle."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 808
msgid ""
"As you might have noticed, I have a few tricks up my sleeve, and one of them "
"is teleportation. When it was evident that our rebellion would not succeed, "
"I cowardly beamed myself out of harm's way. I know, I know, adding shame to "
"disgrace, but such were my younger years."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 812
msgid ""
"I have long since both regretted and repented for my sins, and though it may "
"never be enough, I can now at least live with myself. With myself, haha! No "
"one but good old Luxor..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 816
msgid ""
"Anyway, the Book. Why, pray, would you want it, and why would I give it to "
"you?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 820
msgid ""
"Because it is not for our personal gain! We are on a mission to help my "
"father protect his people from an evil sorcerer, and learning the secrets of "
"his possible futures may be the only way to stop him!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 824
msgid ""
"No need to shout, young lady, and sorry for teasing you. Why, I've known "
"about this possibility ever since you came to the Shadowlands with your beau "
"here."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 828
msgid "My what? Anyway, how did you know?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 832
msgid ""
"How? It was all in the Book, of course! A month ago, I opened it to find a "
"prophecy as clear as day: 'One day, two young warriors will come with others "
"in their stead. First, they will defeat the two Shadowlords. Then, they will "
"survive the Long Night of Shadows. To them, this Book shall be given!'"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 836
msgid ""
"Well, there you go, old man. We've come and we've... Wait, what did you say?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 840
msgid ""
"I must say that the first part of your trial went exceedingly well, and I'm "
"looking forward to the second one."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 844
msgid "Did you say something about surviving another night of shadows?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 848
msgid ""
"The Long Night of Shadows, it's called. I've never seen it but I suppose it "
"should be quite epic. Apparently, all those that the Shadowhounds killed "
"have had their bones taken away, but their spirits were left behind. And it "
"is said that when the Shadowlords are gone, they will rise again with the "
"night, and storm the fortress to exact revenge."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 852
msgid ""
"The night they rise will be especially long and seem longer still, and their "
"numbers will swell by the minute. Should you survive that night, then the "
"Book will be yours."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 856
msgid ""
"Princess! The fates do not like us, but we shall not surrender to them! "
"After all, we have already come this far. Can you help us, old mage, or have "
"you read a prophecy to the contrary?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 860
msgid ""
"No better chance to right at least some of the wrongs of my past, my boy. Of "
"course I shall be with you!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg, line: 870
msgid "And the dwarves! I need to go talk to the dwarves!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [scenario]: id=9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 3
msgid "The Long Night of Shadows"
msgstr ""
#
#. [side]
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 85
msgid "Shadows"
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=win
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 93
msgid "Survive the long night."
msgstr ""
#
#. [objective]: condition=lose
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 97
msgid "Death of Jacques, Kyoko or Luxor."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 135
msgid ""
"Surveying the lines of defense, Jacques wonders at how far a coward such as "
"he has come. All this time spent chasing monsters of one kind or another, "
"and still he could not shed his thievish ways. What was wrong with him, why "
"wouldn't he become what he felt he could be?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 148
msgid ""
"Inspecting the fortress and his troops, Jacques wonders whether he really "
"deserves the respect they pay him. After all, he still feels like nothing "
"more than a simple woodsman, and his battling skills still leave something "
"to be desired."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 158
msgid ""
"The troops get ready for assault, not quite sure where it might come from. "
"Luxor believes that the shadows will come in consecutive waves and from "
"different directions."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 163
msgid ""
"As Jacques walks around encouraging the fighters, he spots Kyoko standing "
"alone at one of the outer walls and walks over."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 168
msgid "Jacques, don't tell anyone, but I'm scared."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 172
msgid "Actually, Princess, so I am. But fear will not paralyze us, will it?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 176
msgid ""
"Please, call me Kyoko. And you're right! One should move swiftly if need be "
"but also stand strong when that is called for! And today, we stand strong!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 190
msgid ""
"Finally, Jacques goes over to the dwellings of the dwarven servants to the "
"Shadowhounds, where at first he is greeted by loud cheers. Choki comes "
"running towards him and shakes his hand, exclaiming loudly that, as "
"promised, his people would now gladly join Jacques and his party."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 195
msgid ""
"Jacques thanks all those present and reiterates how much he also cherishes "
"the reliability of a dwarven promise. Loud cheers and affirmations are heard "
"from the crowd. He goes on to say that such an honor is even more valued at "
"times of great need. This time, the cheers are somewhat more subdued."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 200
msgid ""
"These are such times, I'm afraid, as this fortress is about to be attacked, "
"attacked by the very ghosts of those who have already perished here once "
"before."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 204
msgid ""
"As he speaks, all the cheering ceases. The dwarven faces are painted with "
"concern, some with outright fear. After all, it was them who handled the "
"bodies, and the souls of the fallen might well hold this against them. "
"Besides, what good would be to escape one set of ghosts only to be devoured "
"by another?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 209
msgid ""
"For awhile, Jacques even fears that the dwarves might go back on their word. "
"Then, with a slow resolve, Choki speaks up."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Choki
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 227
msgid ""
"Aye, it is ominous news that you bring here, and our hearts may have "
"darkened again at the prospect of such unfortunate fate. And yet, we did not "
"like the fate that has been dealt to us until today, and we are not slaves "
"that we appear to be. We remember the ancient glory of the dwarves and the "
"honor of our ways. Dark our hearts may be, but darker still will be the day "
"a dwarf swallows his pride and reneges on his word."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 231
msgid ""
"Some dwarves are visibly moved by his words. As for others, they are even "
"more receptive to what Jacques tells them: that the shadows are coming one "
"way or another, and the only chance of defeating them might be coordinating "
"the lines of defense."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 236
msgid ""
"Thus it is finally decided that the dwarves would join in the battle, and it "
"was high time to do so, as the day would pass quickly and the night would "
"soon come..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 251
msgid ""
"Look! The sand is already caving in in some places. It must be those craters "
"that the night shadows will be coming from!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 287
msgid "Stand by for orders, everybody!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 533
msgid ""
"The old mage shot fire bolts and wielded his staff, cackling with each "
"shadow vanishing in thin air. It seemed he fought his inner demons as much "
"as the ones around him. Suddenly, he stood still and his eyes turned white - "
"a hit he didn't see coming struck him hard and he lost consciousness. The "
"shadows that he had fought for so long have taken him at last..."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 560
msgid ""
"After a long night, the first signs of dawn finally emerge. What shadows of "
"the night remain around Jacques and his troops, they slowly grow thinner and "
"finally disappear into the sand."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 574
msgid ""
"With the rise of the new day, Jacques and Kyoko once again meet with Luxor. "
"Luxor insists that they move away from the others and suggests a most "
"improbable place to keep them from being disturbed - one of the clusters of "
"craters from which the shadows have been emerging throughout the long night. "
"Reluctantly, Kyoko and Jacques agree."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 600
msgid "Now we can talk about the Book."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 604
msgid "Yes, the Book of Prophecies! Where is it?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 608
msgid "Ahh, you want to see it? Why of course, here it is."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 616
msgid ""
"A big, prominent book with strange markings appears on the ground before "
"Jacques and Kyoko. Jacques reaches for the book - but as he touches it, he "
"is given an electric shock!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 625
msgid ""
"The book then hisses, transforms into a snake and crawls away, as Luxor "
"cracks with laughter!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 633
msgid ""
"Ahhaha, so impatient, the young are. I knew I should not place the real book "
"before you until you know what awaits you if you take it in your hands. For "
"touching the Book of Prophecies means to become tied to it, much in the way "
"the unfortunate Shadowhounds have once tied their destinies to it."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 637
msgid ""
"So whoever touches the Book eventually meets with this unfortunate fate?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 641
msgid ""
"Not necessarily so, but there are risks. One cannot simply say that he no "
"longer cares about the future, or about the prophecies that are made and may "
"or may not come true."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 645
msgid "But aren't all prophecies always intended to come true?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 649
msgid ""
"Nonsense! Of course not. If they were, you would not be here, for the Book "
"has foretold that you would die tonight."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 653
msgid "But you said nothing of that when we talked yesterday!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 657
msgid ""
"Would you like me to? Of course not. Besides, the Book always shows us "
"several futures, and it is on us to steer our destiny towards one of them. "
"And therein lie both its power and its curse."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Kyoko
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 661
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 666
msgid ""
"He who controls the book has the chance to see how to affect the future, but "
"sometimes it is worse to have such a choice, and to see what the possible "
"outcomes of one's choices are. Ignorance is bliss, hehe!"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Jacques
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 670
msgid ""
"Should we then even take the Book? Can it help us in our fight against "
"Ruphulus?"
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=Luxor
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 674
msgid ""
"Aye, you should and it can. But be careful to know what it is you are doing, "
"for your life will hardly ever be free afterwards."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 682
msgid ""
"Another book appears before them. Crumpled and much less dignified in shape "
"and form, and yet evidently imbued with great potency. Jacques and Kyoko "
"look at each other, and then they reach for the Book simultaneously. As they "
"touch it, nothing happens."
msgstr ""
#
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
# File: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/9_The_Long_Night_of_Shadows.cfg, line: 690
msgid ""
"They look at each other again, and then they turn back towards Luxor to ask "
"if anything special should have happened. But they see the old mage lying "
"collapsed on the ground, dead, with a smile still firmly placed on his face."
msgstr ""
